## Objective
Integrate prompt classifier with beforeResponse hook.

## Tasks
- [ ] Import `classifyPrompt` in `before-response.ts`
- [ ] Add classification call after user message extraction
- [ ] Implement early exit for non-code categories
- [ ] Add detailed logging for classification results
- [ ] Update metadata with classification info
- [ ] Handle UNCLEAR category conservatively

## Implementation

### Location
`skill/src/hooks/before-response.ts` lines 50-70

### Logic
```typescript
import { classifyPrompt, PromptCategory, CODE_CATEGORIES } from '../services/prompt-classifier';

// After getting lastUserMessage
const category = classifyPrompt(lastUserMessage.content);

logger.debug('Prompt classified', {
  category,
  isCodeRelated: CODE_CATEGORIES.includes(category),
  prompt: lastUserMessage.content.slice(0, 80),
});

// Skip non-code prompts
if (!CODE_CATEGORIES.includes(category)) {
  logger.info('Non-code category detected, skipping rule injection', { category });
  return {
    continue: true,
    metadata: { category, skippedRules: true }
  };
}

// Continue with rule selection for code categories...
```

## Files
- `skill/src/hooks/before-response.ts` (UPDATE)

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Non-code prompts skip rule injection
- [ ] Code prompts continue to rule selection
- [ ] Classification logged with context
- [ ] Metadata includes category for debugging
- [ ] Hook still returns continue: true on all paths

## Estimated Effort
2-3 hours

## Objective
Comprehensive test suite for classification and integration.

## Tasks
- [ ] Create `skill/src/services/__tests__/prompt-classifier.test.ts`
- [ ] Test all 9 category classifications
- [ ] Test edge cases (mixed signals like 'financial API')
- [ ] Test pattern matching (legal, HR, etc.)
- [ ] Test keyword scoring fallback
- [ ] Create `skill/src/hooks/__tests__/before-response.integration.test.ts`
- [ ] Test hook skips non-code prompts
- [ ] Test hook injects rules for code prompts
- [ ] Test category-aware boosting
- [ ] Run full test suite and fix failures

## Test Cases

### Unit Tests (prompt-classifier.test.ts)
```typescript
describe('Prompt Classifier', () => {
  test('legal document', () => {
    expect(classifyPrompt('operating agreement financial approval'))
      .toBe(PromptCategory.LEGAL_BUSINESS);
  });

  test('code debugging', () => {
    expect(classifyPrompt('fix the bug in auth.py'))
      .toBe(PromptCategory.CODE_DEBUGGING);
  });

  test('mixed signals - financial API', () => {
    expect(classifyPrompt('add financial reporting API endpoint'))
      .toBe(PromptCategory.CODE_IMPLEMENTATION);
  });

  // ... 12 total test cases from comparison table
});
```

### Integration Tests (before-response.integration.test.ts)
```typescript
describe('beforeResponse with Classification', () => {
  test('skips rules for operating agreement', async () => {
    const result = await handler(createContext('operating agreement rules'));
    expect(result.systemPrompt).toBeUndefined();
    expect(result.metadata.skippedRules).toBe(true);
  });

  test('injects rules for code prompt', async () => {
    const result = await handler(createContext('fix bug in auth.py'));
    expect(result.systemPrompt).toBeDefined();
    expect(result.metadata.rulesLoaded).toBeGreaterThan(0);
  });
});
```

## Files
- `skill/src/services/__tests__/prompt-classifier.test.ts` (NEW)
- `skill/src/hooks/__tests__/before-response.integration.test.ts` (NEW or UPDATE)
- `skill/package.json` (UPDATE - ensure test scripts configured)

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All 12 comparison table test cases pass
- [ ] 0% false positives (all non-code prompts skip)
- [ ] 0% false negatives (all code prompts inject)
- [ ] Edge cases handled correctly
- [ ] Test coverage > 80% for new code
- [ ] All tests pass: `npm test`

## Estimated Effort
4-6 hours

